# SoloStudy - Future Features Brainstorm

## 1. Smart Agenda (LMS Integrations) - Premium Feature

### Canvas/Blackboard Integration

- Users log in with their school credentials
- App fetches assignments, quizzes, and exams via LMS API
- Auto-prioritization: Tasks automatically sorted by due date and weight (exams > quizzes > assignments)
- "Study Mode" button: Next to imported assignments, a single button starts a focus session tagged for that subject
- Sync schedule: Automatic updates when new assignments are added or due dates change

### Benefits

- Eliminates manual task entry
- Context-aware study sessions
- Never miss a deadline

---

## 2. Deep Focus Analytics (Tracking & Aggregation) - Premium Feature

### Chronotype Analysis

- Track when users are most productive
- Insights like: "You complete 30% more tasks between 8 PM and 11 PM"
- Personalized study schedule recommendations

### Distraction Pattern Tracking

- Track pause reasons (Phone, Snack, Noise, etc.)
- Generate reports: "Your #1 distraction is your phone"
- Suggest interventions based on patterns

### Subject Breakdown

- Pie chart showing time distribution across subjects
- Track: 40% Math, 20% History, 40% Procrastinating
- Identify which subjects need more attention

### Focus Heatmap

- GitHub-style contribution graph for study minutes
- Darker green = deeper focus
- Visual representation of study consistency over time

### Session Quality Metrics

- Focus quality score based on interruptions
- Recovery time after distractions
- Completion rate tracking

---

## 3. Study Together (Social Accountability) - Premium Feature

### Virtual Library

- Live view showing "3 other people are studying right now"
- Privacy-first: Don't see video, but see active status, subject, and progress bar
- Optional: Join themed rooms (e.g., "Late Night Study Hall")

### Focus Streaks

- Public or friends-only leaderboards
- Based on "Days in a Row" or "Total Focus Minutes"
- Weekly/monthly challenges

### Accountability Features

- Friend connections and study groups
- Gentle nudges: "Your friend paused their timer - send encouragement?"
- Group goals and shared progress tracking

